WEBPAGE CHECKLIST ( See https://codeburst.io/the-front-end-checklist-8b2292fdda44 for more detail)


HTML

doctype 
	<!doctype html>

html[lang] set to correct language
	<html lang="fr">

rtl
	<html dir="rtl">

alternate languages
	<link rel="alternate" href="https://es.example.com/" hreflang="es">

IE Conditionals
	Conditional comments are present for IE if needed.

Critical CSS Inlined
	inline critical CSS: CSS which styles content that is immediately visible during pageload (“above the fold content”) is called “critical CSS”. It is embedded before your principal CSS call and between <style></style> in a single line (minified).

Import order
	All CSS files are loaded before any JavaScript files 

encoding set 
	<meta charset="utf-8">

title set 
	<title>Page Title less than 65 characters</title>

description 
	<meta name="description" content="Description of the page less than 150 characters">

author set

favicon 
	see https://css-tricks.com/favicon-quiz/ & realfavicon webpage
	and https://github.com/audreyr/favicon-cheat-sheet
	e.g.<link rel="icon" type="image/png" href="https://example.com/favicon.png"> 

???? x-ua-compatible 
	<meta http-equiv="x-ua-compatible" content="ie=edge">

???? viewport
	<meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">

SRI (Subresource Integrity)
	used on remotely loaded resources from CDN etc.



CSS

Web Fonts
	Webfont format: WOFF, WOFF2 and TTF are supported by all modern browsers.

CSS Print
	Print stylesheet present

Inline CSS
	Should not exist

CSS Concatenated into single file & minified


Responsive
	All pages were tested at the following breakpoints: 320px, 768px, 1024px



IMAGES
	
Alt Text
	Images have alt text

Optimization
	All images are optimized to be rendered in the browser. WebP format could be used for critical pages (like Homepage).


JAVASCRIPT

No inline
	No inline

Javascript files concatenated & minified

Linting
	ESLint: No errors are flagged by ESLint


SECURITY
	securityheaders.io
	Observatory by Mozilla

Use HTTPS 
	On all pages

Lots of other stuff on
	https://codeburst.io/the-front-end-checklist-8b2292fdda44


VALIDATION

Internationalisation
	https://validator.w3.org/unicorn/ 

Links
	https://validator.w3.org/checklink 

HTML Lint
	https://www.10bestdesign.com/dirtymarkup/


SEO

Google Analytics: 
	Google Analytics is installed and correctly configured.

Headings logic: 
	Heading text helps to understand the content in the current page.

sitemap.xml: 
	A sitemap.xml exists and was submitted to Google Search Console (previously Google Webmaster Tools).

robots.txt: 
	The robots.txt is not blocking webpages.